        <h2>Your responsibility for inputs and outputs</h2>
        <p>You are responsible for what you paste into a tool and how you use the result. Always review output before shipping it to production.</p>
        <p>Example: if you minify JSON here and then deploy it, that final deployment decision is still yours, not ours.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="static-page__section">
        <h2>Data and privacy expectations</h2>
        <p>Most tools are designed to run directly in your browser. Some platform-level telemetry and operational logs may still be collected to keep the service healthy and secure.</p>
        <p>Do not submit secrets, credentials, or regulated personal data unless your team has approved that workflow.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="static-page__section">
        <h2>Service availability</h2>
        <p>I try to keep ToolNexus fast and available, but uptime is not guaranteed. Features can change, improve, or be removed over time.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="static-page__section">
        <h2>Liability (plain version)</h2>
        <p>ToolNexus is provided as-is. We are not liable for losses or damages caused by using the platform, including output errors, downtime, or workflow interruptions.</p>
    </section>

